> -Finally, I've read about pop tops for Westies being easy to replace, but
> what about for Rivieras?  This is the only one I haven't tried to look up,
> so apologies if the info is at my fingertips somewhere.  Does anyone sell
> reproductions (e.g. yellow vinyl straight-up pop tops)?
> 
They're hard to find.  I looked and looked for a Riviera top, couldn't find
one in good shape.  Decided to put a Westy top on the Riviera- they're easy
to find.  Also, you can use Westy seals on Riviera tops.  Replacement
canvases are available.

Have fun, Nik
